messages.msgSnippet: In a message dated 6/30/03 8:33:17 AM Eastern Daylight Time, ... I think there are a couple of state parks that have beach access and camping sites.  Not sure
messages.messageBody:
In a message dated 6/30/03 8:33:17 AM Eastern Daylight Time,
Tuckervill@... writes:

> We're going after, somewhere down by the coast. But we want to camp on the
>
> beach. Does anyone know if you can do such a thing in SC?
>
>

I think there are a couple of state parks that have beach access and camping
sites. Not sure if they charge. I don't think you can go out on the beach at
random and camp for the night. I do think I read something about that
somewhere.
<A HREF="http://www.funbeaches.com/campgrounds.html">Myrtle Beach State Parks and Campgrounds</A>

I can't remember if this list supports links if it does this is a link to
Myrtle beach campgrounds.

If not it is <A HREF="http://www.funbeaches.com/campgrounds.html">http://www.funbeaches.com/campgrounds.html</A>

Pam G.
